caption: I went on my first run in what seems like forever. I didn't run out of competition, to PR or weight loss, I just ran for myself. After a healed injury while marathon training a few yrs ago, I struggled with the fact that I wasn't as fast as I was in the past and it was always an inner competition with myself that lead to burnout. I got over the fear today and was in total bliss. I may have been SLOW MO but it was the best run I've had in years bc the past is behind me and I'm now in the present. I guess a focus in strength training left me feeling stronger than I ever had on a run. Cheers to Friday, being fearless and living in the moment, oh and Central Park 🙏🏻
